Package itl.enabler.api

The core forecourt classes needed by your application to connect to the Enabler

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Attendant.AttendantEventListener
    Event Listener for the Attendant class
    AttendantCollection.AttendantCollectionEventListener
    Listens to events from every Attendant in the collection.
    Clients can either implement this interface to receive events on the whole Attendant Collection or subscribe to events from individual attendantsByNum.
    Fallback.FallBackModeEventListener
    Event Listener for the Fallback class
    Forecourt.ForecourtEventListener
    Event listener for the Forecourt class
    Grade.GradeEventListener
    Event Listener for the Grade class
    GradeCollection.GradeCollectionEventListener
    Listens to events from every Grade in the collection.
    Clients can either implement this interface to receive events on the whole Grade Collection or subscribe to events from individual gradesByNum.
    Hose.HoseEventListener
    Event Listener for the Hose class
    HoseCollection.HoseCollectionEventListener
    Listens to events from every Hose in the collection.
    Clients can either implement this interface to receive events on the whole Hose Collection or subscribe to events from individual hoses.
    Pump.PumpEventListener
    Event Listener for the Pump class
    PumpCollection.PumpCollectionEventListener
    Listens to events from every Pump in the collection.
    Clients can either implement this interface to receive events on the whole Pump Collection or subscribe to events from individual pumpsByNum.
    Tank.TankEventListener
    Event Listener for the Tank class
    TankCollection.TankCollectionEventListener
    Listens to events from every Tank in the collection.
    Clients can either implement this interface to receive events on the whole Tank Collection or subscribe to events from individual tanksByNum.
    Terminal.TerminalEventListener
    Event Listener for the Terminal class
    TerminalCollection.TerminalCollectionEventListener
    Listens to events from every Terminal in the collection.
    Clients can either implement this interface to receive events on the whole Terminal Collection or subscribe to events from individual terminalsByNum.
